Name: tuco
Version: 0.3.0
Summary: A simple class based finite state machine with parsing time validation
Home-page: https://github.com/eatfirst/python-tuco
Author: EatFirst
Author-email: it+opensource@eatfirst.com
License: MIT license
Description: ========
        Overview
        ========
        
        
        
        A simple class based finite state machine with parsing time validation
        
        * Free software: MIT license
        
        Installation
        ============
        
        ::
        
            pip install tuco
        
        Documentation
        =============
        
        https://python-tuco.readthedocs.io/
        
        Development
        ===========
        Make sure you have a running redis instance and to run the all tests run::
        
            tox
        
        Note, to combine the coverage data from all the tox environments run:
        
        .. list-table::
            :widths: 10 90
            :stub-columns: 1
        
            - - Windows
              - ::
        
                    set PYTEST_ADDOPTS=--cov-append
                    tox
        
            - - Other
              - ::
        
                    PYTEST_ADDOPTS=--cov-append tox
        
        
        Changelog
        =========
        
        0.3.0
        -----
        
        - Fix: Propagate existing __classcell__ to fix a DeprecationWarning.
        
        0.2.0
        -----
        
        - Feature: Add get_all_states() method.
        
        0.1.0
        -----
        
        - Initial release.
        
